a:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Who Should Choose Which?"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"The ideal user for each platform differs considerably. Craiyon is best suited for casual fun, memes, quick sketches, beginners, making it a strong choice if you fall into any of these categories. StarryAI, meanwhile, shines for mobile art creation, NFT art, casual generation, on the go creativity, which means it may be the better pick if your needs align with those use cases.\n\nFounded in 2022, Craiyon describes itself as \"Free AI image generator formerly known as DALL-E Mini.\" StarryAI, established in 2021, positions itself as \"Mobile-first AI art generator with NFT minting support.\" Both platforms have been in the market for a similar duration, giving each ample time to refine their offerings and build a loyal user base."}]]}]
b:["$","div",null,{"className":"verdict-box","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Our Verdict"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"After analyzing all the data, **StarryAI** comes out slightly ahead in this comparison, thanks to higher user ratings (5.0 vs 4.0), availability of a free plan. However, this does not mean Craiyon is a poor choice — far from it. Craiyon excels in its own right, particularly for casual fun and memes.\n\nOur recommendation: if you value good mobile app experience, go with StarryAI. If completely free to use matters more to you, Craiyon is the way to go. Either way, both are solid platforms that have earned their place in the market."}]]}]
